{"id":14880863,"mediaExerciseId":"617ed84a-0b0e-4e9f-a121-93ad839d5304","exerciseName":"16","chapterName":"4","chapterTitle":"Long-Term Financial Planning and Growth","groupId":612285,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":119,"solutions":[{"id":5951529,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise will require us to compute the growth of sales of Hodgkiss Manufacturing Inc. before any fixed assets are needed.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/28/87badcda59e37b1cd2849c0667cb39b9/38f87da0b83b03f6b3f703f88e8170bb/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/28/87badcda59e37b1cd2849c0667cb39b9/38f87da0b83b03f6b3f703f88e8170bb/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"### Let's first give the data in the problem.\n\n* The fixed assets are not fully functional and currently operate at 91%.\n\n* Current Sales are $715,000.00","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement.\n\n### The maximum growth of sales before any fixed assets are required.\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"### First, compute the total capacity of sales.\n\nThe full capacity of sales is calculated by dividing the current sales by the operating ability of the assets.\n\nThe formula and computation are as follows.\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Full Capacity of Sales} &= \\dfrac{\\text{Current Sales}}{\\text{Operating Capacity of Asset}}\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\dfrac{\\$715,000.00}{91\\%}\\\\[15pt]\n\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{\\$785,714.29}}\n\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\nTherefore, the full capacity of sales is **$785,714.29**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"### Compute the maximum growth without additional assets.\n\nThe maximum growth is calculated by dividing total capacity with the current sales of less than one.\n\nThe formula and computation are as follows.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Max Growth of Sales} &= \\dfrac{\\text{Full Capacity of Sales}}{\\text{Current Sales}}- 1\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\dfrac{\\$785,714.29}{\\$715,000.00}-1\\\\[15pt]\n\n&= 1.0989 - 1 \\\\[15pt]\n\n&= 0.0989 \\times 100\\\\[15pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{9.89\\%}}\n\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n\nThe maximum growth of sales without the need for additional assets is **9.89%**.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"faf475e0-824c-4ccc-95c1-e506a338cc89","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880864,"exerciseName":"17","page":119,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"57ba5d63-c43d-4d70-aa15-8adc9f7b1131","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-4-question